title: Dead Man's Switch
description: Prejudiced thugs attack a Puerto Rican teen at the neighborhood youth center, egged into action by the columns of a bigoted writer. As his son lies near death in the hospital, the boy's father pays the race-baiting writer a visit--armed with a hand grenade.

title: The Night of the Precious Stones
National Treasure
description: Manfred is called to the estate of Lord Eastly for a deathbed confession: the Rembrandt painting hanging in his home is an original. It had been stolen from the museum and replaced with a copy. The lord wants Manfred to return the painting as quietly as possible.

title: The Man with the Golden Touch
Marie
description: Tim saves a woman from jumping off a bridge into the Seine River. After coming to at his apartment, he and Nicole learn only her name, Marie, and that she's from Algeria before running off. Wanting to help, Tim tracks down the young woman's uncle who says she smuggled herself into France to escape the political horrors back home.

title: The Discovery
description: An unlicensed doctor is accused of murdering a sick friend by using him as a Guinea pig, administering an experimental drug he devised.

title: Crack-Up
description: A plane which crashed five years earlier is spotted by a hunter in Canada. Jeff is visited by the late pilot's wife. She wants him to get to the wreckage first to see if a half-million dollars of embezzled gold was aboard the aircraft.

title: The Miracle of St. Phillipe
description: Collier and Nicole arrive in a small French town filled with pilgrims seeking miracles from a holy relic. When it's stolen, a crazy man confesses, but he eagerly takes the blame for any and all crimes anyway.

title: The Man in the Royal Suite
The Grandmother
description: An old French military family has a shameful secret to hide about how a troop of soldiers lost their lives, and how the matriarchal grandmother's own grandson lost his sight in the Algerian war.

title: The Man Who Wasn't There
description: Manfred's investigates a possibly kidnapped scientist takes him to a reactivated, but top secret Royal Navy station on a small island off Scotland. Though an MP, he's refused entry. He sneaks in, locating the missing man, in an old shed.

title: The Last Days of Nick Pompey
Treviso Dam
description: After a young man working on a new multimillion-Lira dam project tells Poccari of some of the dangerously inferior cement being used, he has a mysterious fatal accident. So Poccari goes to investigate.
